<media id="fs-id1167663970698" alt="a) Diagram of a normal nerve cell releasing acetylcholine which binds to receptors on the muscle cell. This signal is processed and the muscle cell contracts. B) Diagram of myasthenia gravis. The nerve cell releases acetylcholine but anti-AChR antibodies bind to the acetylcholine so it cannot bind to the receptors on the muscle cells. Because the signal is blocked the muscle is paralyzed and does not contract.">
